comments.body:
This
- Fixes how `make test-system` unnecessarily overrides `storage.conf` in CI.
- Attempts to fix, apparently long-unused, `make test-integration` and `make test-system` running in containers, for developers’ on-workstation use. At least it fixes the failure in #1222, but I didn’t yet actually get this _working_. But apparently it’s not being used, so that’s not nearly as important as the CI.
- Updates c/storage to 1.45.3, the version that is failing without the changes, as a demonstration.

@rhatdan PTAL.

@cevich FYI (non-urgent), this points at a part of the reason of the recent Podman trouble - changing `storage.conf` under a pre-existing Podman database seems to make it unhappy. Now that we don’t do that, that workaround is no longer necessary.
